def _unstack_multiple(data, clocs, fill_value=None):
    if len(clocs) == 0:
        return data

    index = data.index
    columns = data.columns

    cnames = [c if isinstance(c, str) else c[-1] for c in clocs]

    unstacked = data.unstack(clocs, fill_value=fill_value)

    multi_columns = isinstance(unstacked.columns, MultiIndex)
    
    if multi_columns:
        new_columns = MultiIndex.from_tuples(
            [
                (col1, col2) if not isinstance(col1, tuple) else col1 + (col2,)
                for col1, col2 in unstacked.columns
            ],
            names=[(name1, name2) if not isinstance(name2, str) else (None, name2)
                   for name1, name2 in unstacked.columns.names]
        )
    else:
        new_columns = MultiIndex.from_tuples(
            [(col, name) for col, name in zip(unstacked.columns, cnames)],
            names=[None, clocs]
        )

    unstacked.columns = new_columns

    return unstacked
